76561198066945741,Not Recommended,222140,33093554,Posted: 1 July,all,Z0RM4N,"Puddle is a platform-ish game. You have to move your puddle of liquid around the different levels. You don't have full control over the liquid though. The liquid moves depending on gravity and momentum (or other factors, depending on which level you're at). All you can do is angle the screen left or right, making the liquid move that way. The angling also helps you slow down or speed up your liquid. You only need 2 buttons, left and right. The liquids you control differ from level to level. Sometimes, it's a thick goo that sticks well together, othertimes it's an explosive goo that explodes when it crashes against a surface.Looking at the levels, they really look nice. Graphically, this game is beautiful. Gameplaywise though, some can feel really unfair. You can't see what's ahead, so finishing a level on the first try is very difficult. There are a couple levels where it's not very well explained what you need to do or how the physics have changed from the previous level. There are no checkpoints in any level, meaning you need to complete the entire level in one go. Most of the levels are however quite short.The game doesn't store its info on the steam servers, so if you uninstall the game, you lose all your progress.Looking back, I like the idea, but too many levels feel unfair and become unfun. I don't recommand this game. If you want to try this, buy it when on sale."
