,Not Recommended,222140,9411878,"Posted: 10 March, 2014",all,Zell,"*Edited the review since the major bugs and crashes have been fixed. However, I still do not recommend this game, as it is not really FUN. This however, is according to my personal taste, so I will elaborate further.=================================================================This game seems at first to remind me of fun titles such as World of Goo, Nightsky, and other physics based platformers with objects to control.(-) However, its more frustrating, as the liquid is not as controllable as you'd expect. Most times, it is quite random how much liquid you'd lose along the way, so getting a gold medal depends more on luck (and trying a million times) rather than having perfect control of the ""physics"".(-) The game has options to assign different ""left"" and ""right"" for the liquid and for the environment, but this simply doesn't work. It makes the game unplayable. Not sure why they have these settings when all you need are 2 keys to play the game.(+) This I suppose makes it a pro for keyboard players, since you don't need an XBOX controller to play this game, like many steam games nowadays.(+) Another good point is that there is a lot of variety. You will ""handle"" different liquids in different environments. The artistic value is there, and it does show that the developers tried with this game.(-) The variety however is pretty much summed up in the two lines above. You will not have to use your brain or solve puzzles to progress. You simply follow the linear path, trying to avoid obstacles or things that will reduce the amount of liquid you have. You WILL lose liquid. The point is trying to get to the end with enough to progress to the next level.Unfortunately, this game simply isn't as fun as the games mentioned above.I have played many games. Some pull you in. Some repel you. This game does neither. For this I am still inclined to open it up and play it to the end, but at the same time I'm not really having as fun as I do with games that do pull me in.There isn't a challenge per se. You go from A to B without any chance to deviate from the path.I still open this game up from time to time, as I like to complete my games. But this one is taking a while since I don't have fun when I do. It's not a BAD game though, but it's not one that I can recommend."
,Recommended,222140,10166863,"Posted: 18 May, 2014",all,TeamKiller[153],"Puddle is a Physics based puzzle game where you control various liquids, by tilting the screen using the left and right arrows on your keyboard. Each liquid has it's own properties, and you must use those inorder to navigate your way to the exit, past obsticles and hazards all the while keeping as much substince as possible. Personally I thought the first half of the game was actually kindof fun and creative. Each ""chapter"" gives you time to learn about the new liquid, and the transitions between each are quite creative. However besides the human body chapter, the second half of the game is just painfully hard. I'm not saying I don't like a little challenge now and then, but when you have to be almost flawless to get enough liquid to the end, it's kindof off putting. The Foundry level is what really tested my patients, so much in fact that 6 months ago (atleast) I gave up and didn't  even atempt trying until today, and beat it. Never before has a game made me so frusterated, that I just gave up, and I'm a very patient person. Ask anybody! Now the game does allow you to skip upto 4 levels if you find them too hard, but I could not bring myself to do such a thing. While this game does have a a rather high difficulty, it looks very preaty and is quite fun at the begining. I would not recommend this to anyone who does not have the patients to complete the game, but if you are willing (and it's on sale) then give it a look see. It might just surprise you. Still cheaper on iOS though.***"
